## Portfolio Summary

This five-stock portfolio balances growth, profitability, and sector diversification across Financial Services, Biotechnology, Semiconductors, Software, and Engineering/Construction. The portfolio is anchored by two high-conviction, profitable growth stories (SoFi and Krystal Biotech) that offer both revenue acceleration and valuation support, complemented by three quality large-cap and mid-cap names (Qualcomm, Cloudflare, Fluor) positioned to benefit from secular AI infrastructure buildout, cloud computing adoption, and industrial sector rotation. Risk profile is moderate to moderately-aggressive: the top two picks carry lower valuation risk with proven profitability, while the remaining three offer growth catalysts offset by elevated valuation multiples (Cloudflare, Qualcomm) or cyclical exposure (Fluor). Overall, the portfolio reflects conviction in technology infrastructure tailwinds, fintech disruption, biotech innovation, and industrial cycle recovery, with intentional sector diversification to reduce concentration risk. All five companies carry A or B investment grades with strong fundamental support, eliminating any C or D-rated candidates from consideration.